-- Indian shares edge higher in cautious trade
-- By Indulal PM
-- Thu Aug 21, 2014 06:07AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Aug 21 (Reuters) - Indian shares edged higher on Thursday for a seventh session of gains in the past eight, as continued buying by foreign investors bolstered blue-chips such as State Bank of India <SBI.NS>.

The benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> provisionally closed 0.17 percent higher at 26,360.11 points, while the broader NSE index <.NSEI> ended up 0.2 percent at 7,891.10.